text: This stall former by old woman, now I think is 2nd Generation. Porridge is nice and meat, tofu, pig skin is generous and taste nice only S$8.00 for this meal. üëç

If you are lucky, u can pick up a couple of pretty blouses at $10, $20 when they r on sale.

This is the department store to go to for reasonably-priced merchandise. Love the 3-ply Darling pocket tissues at $3 for 3 packs of 10s. Good quality 1000ml hand/body wash. About $4.

Not for snobs but for smart fashionistas who know how to dollar stretch AND still look good. Chic on the cheap.

For a local people or senior citizen and overseas tourists, if you want to eat very full and good food, try this store at Chinatown Complex hawker centre,  it tasty and very cheap and the meat like BBQ pork, chicken and duck he will sell all finish that is why all the meat it very fresh.  if I not mistaken in Singapore you still cannot find $2:00 chicken rice. The store number is 02-181, Uncle and Auntie they are both Singaporean they work for young until this old age.

So full of all those cliches souvenir stores that sell cheap throwaway quality products,  and eateries that are catered for mainland Chinese taste (distinctly different to local Chinese). At least it's neat, but seriously,  you can do a lot better than spending time and money here.
